00:02:51.431 --> 00:02:53.410
>> JOE A. SIMPSON JR.:
I was laid out flat

00:02:53.411 --> 00:02:55.849
on a cold, hard operating table,

00:02:55.850 --> 00:02:58.385
similar to the one that you see here,

00:02:58.386 --> 00:03:00.854
and as the anesthesiologist
put the mask on,

00:03:00.855 --> 00:03:02.856
I began to count backwards.

00:03:02.857 --> 00:03:07.896
100, 99, 98.

00:03:09.097 --> 00:03:11.498
As I slowly drifted off to sleep,

00:03:11.499 --> 00:03:14.673
all I could think about
were these faces.

00:03:17.005 --> 00:03:20.874
Just yesterday,
I was seated at the kitchen table,

00:03:20.875 --> 00:03:24.412
my wife here, my daughter to my left,

00:03:25.246 --> 00:03:29.650
and I had to do the hardest
thing I've ever done in my life.

00:03:29.651 --> 00:03:34.053
We decided not to tell my daughter
about the surgical procedure

00:03:34.054 --> 00:03:36.423
because she was in the final
year of high school.

00:03:36.424 --> 00:03:40.561
She was preparing
her portfolio to go to art school.

00:03:40.562 --> 00:03:43.498
She was a creative,
just like her dad,

00:03:44.666 --> 00:03:47.602
and we didn't want to interrupt that.

00:03:47.736 --> 00:03:49.803
It was at the same kitchen table

00:03:49.804 --> 00:03:55.143
where I would sit
her on the table as a child,

00:03:55.210 --> 00:03:57.411
a little toddler,
and she would jump into my arms.

00:03:57.412 --> 00:03:59.813
I would take a step back,
she would jump again,

00:03:59.814 --> 00:04:03.918
and we would do it over
and over and over again.

00:04:04.019 --> 00:04:05.052
But on this day,

00:04:05.053 --> 00:04:09.813
I had to do the hardest thing
I've ever had to do in my life.

00:04:11.259 --> 00:04:13.160
I had to tell
her that there was a possibility

00:04:13.161 --> 00:04:17.287
that I wouldn't be coming
home tomorrow at this time.

00:04:17.866 --> 00:04:20.759
As I came to and left the hospital,

00:04:21.569 --> 00:04:25.806
I decided to take a leave of absence,
a 90-day leave of absence

00:04:25.807 --> 00:04:28.375
to heal physically and mentally.

00:04:28.376 --> 00:04:31.146
I had two 100% blocked arteries,

00:04:32.313 --> 00:04:36.083
and it would take
all that I had to get back.

00:04:36.084 --> 00:04:39.953
I wanted to rediscover things
that gave me creative joy,

00:04:39.954 --> 00:04:42.122
and I wanted to define a new journey,

00:04:42.123 --> 00:04:44.691
but just getting out
of bed was difficult.

00:04:44.692 --> 00:04:47.194
My road back led me to the outdoors.

00:04:47.195 --> 00:04:51.321
I visited every outdoor
park in Santa Clarita Valley,

00:04:51.966 --> 00:04:53.033
putting one foot in front

00:04:53.034 --> 00:04:58.038
of the other till 1 foot
became 10 feet,

00:04:58.039 --> 00:05:00.684
which became a quarter of a lap,

00:05:00.742 --> 00:05:03.243
then a full lap, until one day,

00:05:03.244 --> 00:05:07.687
I was at the base of the hill
that you see on your right.

00:05:08.116 --> 00:05:11.518
At the top of this hill,
it was the highest point

00:05:11.519 --> 00:05:14.931
in the Santa Clarita
Valley at Central Park.

00:05:15.056 --> 00:05:16.990
I decided before I went back to work

00:05:16.991 --> 00:05:21.362
in 90 days that I would get
to the top of this hill,

00:05:23.731 --> 00:05:27.539
but 5 days before I returned
to work in December,

00:05:28.336 --> 00:05:33.808
this is the view that I saw
just before sunrise,

00:05:35.977 --> 00:05:38.913
overlooking the Santa Clarita Valley.

00:05:43.651 --> 00:05:45.064
