When you're organizing a team,
try to be as inclusive as possible

00:14:45.760 --> 00:14:47.794
in terms of the people
that you invite

00:14:47.795 --> 00:14:51.165
to organize, the volunteers,
and speakers.

00:14:52.600 --> 00:14:55.969
They offer perspectives
that you may not have.

00:14:55.970 --> 00:14:58.959
Offer a seat at the table
for outspoken voices

00:14:58.960 --> 00:15:02.451
as resources, collaborators,
and inspiration.

00:15:02.710 --> 00:15:04.609
One of the things
that I pride myself on

00:15:04.610 --> 00:15:07.748
is that in the WordPress space,

00:15:07.948 --> 00:15:11.686
there are so many important
and eclectic voices.

00:15:13.721 --> 00:15:16.322
People are always sharing
their information with each other.

00:15:16.323 --> 00:15:18.242
People are always trying
to help each other,

00:15:18.243 --> 00:15:20.482
so I try to incorporate
as many of those voices

00:15:20.483 --> 00:15:25.005
in the decisions that I make in terms
of organizing event.

00:15:26.934 --> 00:15:30.637
I also suggest you leverage
pre-existing efforts.

00:15:30.638 --> 00:15:33.473
There's articles and information.

00:15:33.474 --> 00:15:34.974
There's things on Make.

00:15:34.975 --> 00:15:37.377
There's things on the blog
that you can tap

00:15:37.378 --> 00:15:41.014
into to help
you make informed decisions.

00:15:41.015 --> 00:15:45.251
The other cool thing that happened
was when I published that document,

00:15:45.252 --> 00:15:49.022
and again, I'll share
