00:15:55.730 --> 00:15:58.531
One of the first things
that I always suggest

00:15:58.532 --> 00:15:59.666
if you're planning an event

00:15:59.667 --> 00:16:03.504
like a WordCamp
is to scout the venue.

00:16:03.838 --> 00:16:07.107
A lot of times,
a decision on a venue is made

00:16:07.108 --> 00:16:10.610
without touring the venue, or maybe

00:16:10.611 --> 00:16:13.880
it's without touring the venue
with people that are aware

00:16:13.881 --> 00:16:16.249
of accessibility and can look

00:16:16.250 --> 00:16:19.052
at the venue in terms
of how accessible it is,

00:16:19.053 --> 00:16:21.642
and if there are any issues
that need to be addressed

00:16:21.643 --> 00:16:26.861
that could be major
problems in terms of the event.

00:16:26.961 --> 00:16:28.528
One of the stories
that I like to share

00:16:28.529 --> 00:16:32.098
was when I was on the team
as a captain for WordCamp US,

00:16:32.099 --> 00:16:33.448
when it was in San Diego,

00:16:33.449 --> 00:16:36.102
it was at a really incredible
location.

00:16:36.103 --> 00:16:39.673
It was a retro resort
called Town and Country.

00:16:40.574 --> 00:16:41.941
It had the '50s vibe.

00:16:41.942 --> 00:16:45.512
The architecture looked
like it was from the '50s modernist.

00:16:45.513 --> 00:16:47.592
Unfortunately,
it was one of the worst conferences

00:16:47.593 --> 00:16:49.816
in terms of the venue
being accessible,

00:16:49.817 --> 00:16:53.186
and there were a number of problems
in terms of accessibility.

00:16:53.187 --> 00:16:55.855
Michelle Frechette
wrote an incredible article

00:16:55.856 --> 00:17:00.378
on the experiences that she had
trying to get in doorways,

00:17:00.699 --> 00:17:03.952
there were no elevators,
things like that.

00:17:05.666 --> 00:17:09.569
I try to take this information in,
and I try to use it in terms

00:17:09.570 --> 00:17:12.049
of the events that I organize.

00:17:12.139 --> 00:17:14.240
Again, tour the venue
as early as possible,

00:17:14.241 --> 00:17:16.042
ideally with someone
that has a disability.

00:17:16.043 --> 00:17:20.614
Get the physical venue
for things that may be an issue.

00:17:20.881 --> 00:17:24.184
Are the entrances open?

00:17:24.185 --> 00:17:25.318
Are they wide enough?

00:17:25.319 --> 00:17:29.757
Bathrooms, conference spaces,
auditoriums,

00:17:31.091 --> 00:17:34.360
do they have paddles,
handles, and counter heights

00:17:34.361 --> 00:17:38.866
that are accessible to someone
in an assistive device?

