00:23:16.670 --> 00:23:20.173
I suggested we have a dedicated
accessibility team

00:23:20.174 --> 00:23:25.111
as one of the core
teams on a WordCamp.

00:23:25.112 --> 00:23:29.071
Generally, accessibility
is part of attendee experience,

00:23:29.072 --> 00:23:30.883
so we work closely with them,

00:23:30.884 --> 00:23:33.953
but we also wanted
to have more direct input

00:23:33.954 --> 00:23:38.357
on all the teams in terms
of suggesting accessible fixes

00:23:38.358 --> 00:23:40.726
or things in terms
of accessibility practices

00:23:40.727 --> 00:23:44.059
that we wanted to see
throughout the event.

00:23:44.164 --> 00:23:48.624
When I posted my suggestions on Make

00:23:49.502 --> 00:23:51.537
for making events accessible,

00:23:51.538 --> 00:23:55.875
I heard from someone named
Ryan Bourne, who, disability,

00:23:55.876 --> 00:23:57.310
and he suggested a number of ways

00:23:57.311 --> 00:23:59.912
that we can make WordCamp
US accessible,

00:23:59.913 --> 00:24:01.214
and again, I love collaborating.

00:24:01.215 --> 00:24:04.050
I love learning,
so he suggested a number of things

00:24:04.051 --> 00:24:07.225
that we were able
to incorporate as well.

00:24:07.521 --> 00:24:11.424
He has issues in large crowds,

00:24:11.425 --> 00:24:16.496
so he suggested offering distance
badges to let attendees know

00:24:17.130 --> 00:24:20.299
your level of comfort in terms
of being around other people.

00:24:20.300 --> 00:24:21.980
We implemented that.

00:24:23.170 --> 00:24:25.404
Also, I mentioned we work

00:24:25.405 --> 00:24:27.873
closely with the Attendee
Experience Team,

00:24:27.874 --> 00:24:30.644
and then also, I would suggest

00:24:31.578 --> 00:24:34.213
briefing other teams,
like the volunteers,

00:24:34.214 --> 00:24:38.784
on accessibility-specific
instructions

00:24:38.785 --> 00:24:42.055
in terms of how the event should go.

00:24:42.723 --> 00:24:44.591
The event live stream.

00:24:44.992 --> 00:24:49.262
Offer low-capacity viewing
rooms or quiet rooms

00:24:49.263 --> 00:24:51.898
for neurodivergent attendees,

00:24:54.901 --> 00:24:57.038
live captioned program presentations,

00:24:57.039 --> 00:25:01.808
and consider using ASL
for at least a keynote.

00:25:02.909 --> 00:25:05.945
